==Standard dialogue==
* '''Longbow Ben:''' Arrr, matey!
* {{tcond|Before completing [[Pirate's Treasure]]:}}
** {{topt|I'm looking for Redbeard Frank.}}
*** '''Player:''' I'm looking for Redbeard Frank.
*** '''Longbow Ben:''' Redbeard Frank ye say? He be outside. Says he likes the feel of the wind on his cheeks.
*** '''Player:''' Thanks.
*** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Why are you called Longbow Ben?}}
** '''Player:''' Why are you called Longbow Ben?
** '''Longbow Ben:''' Arrr, that's a strange yarn.
** '''Longbow Ben:''' I was to be marooned, ye see. A scurvy troublemaker had taken my ship, and he put me ashore on a little island.
** '''Player:''' Gosh, how did you escape?
** '''Longbow Ben:''' Arrr, ye see, he made one mistake! Before he sailed away, he gave me a bow and one arrow so that I wouldn't have to die slowly.
** '''Longbow Ben:''' So I shot him and took my ship back.
** '''Player:''' Right...
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Have you got any quests I could do?}}
** '''Player:''' Have you got any quests I could do?
** {{tcond|Before completing [[Pirate's Treasure]] and [[Goblin Diplomacy]]:}}
*** '''Longbow Ben:''' Nay, but the barkeep hears most of the news around here. Or Redbeard Frank, he's often spoken of buried treasure. Perhaps ye should be asking them for quests.
*** '''Player:''' Thanks.
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{tcond|Before completing [[Pirate's Treasure]]:}}
*** '''Longbow Ben:''' Nay, but Redbeard Frank has often spoken of buried treasure. Perhaps ye should be asking him for a quest.
*** '''Player:''' Thanks.
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{tcond|Before completing [[Goblin Diplomacy]]:}}
*** '''Longbow Ben:''' Nay, but the barkeep hears most of the news around here. Perhaps ye should be asking him for a quest.
*** '''Player:''' Thanks.
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{tcond|After completing [[Pirate's Treasure]] and [[Goblin Diplomacy]]:}}
*** '''Longbow Ben:''' Nay, I've nothing for ye to do. But I hear there's an old landlubber in Draynor Village who's always a-looking for a lively [lad/lass] to do him a favour.
*** '''Player:''' Thanks.
*** {{tact|end}}

==Alternate dialogue==
* '''Jack Seagull:''' Arrr, matey!
* '''Longbow Ben:''' Yo ho ho!
* '''Player:''' So are you pirates?
* '''Longbow Ben:''' Aye laddie, that we are.
* '''Jack Seagull:''' Aye, that we be.
* '''Longbow Ben:''' Nay, always ye say it wrong! Tis 'we are', not 'we be'.
* '''Jack Seagull:''' I be a pirate, not a scurvy schoolmaster!
* '''Longbow Ben:''' Ye be a fool, and a disgrace to piracy.
* '''Jack Seagull:''' Now ye be saying 'be' too!
* '''Longbow Ben:''' Arrr! Tis thy fault.
* '''Player:''' I think I'll leave you two to sort it out.
* {{tact|end}}
